While not a snow tire specifically, fresh Hankooks perform adequately
in winter conditions.

Of course, as others have suggested, knowing how to drive in winter
conditions is crucial, perhaps as important as the tires themselves.

I have also found that having the rear brakes working and adjusted
properly is important in a winter hard stop situation.

